People nowadays are talking about whether teenagers should make decisions independently or with guidance from others. Some people argue that teenagers should make decisions with guidance from others. I firmly believe that making decisions for themselves is a better choice. This essay will demonstrate this through education and clothing choices.

First and foremost, choosing which subject to study is one of the most important decisions in a person's academic career and should be decided by the teenagers themselves. This is because teenagers generally know what they want, and they have the right to pursue their dreams. It can be computer science, artificial intelligence, medicine, or many other fields. If teenagers had listened to others' advice instead of following their own interests, they would probably have lost the life they wanted.

Another important consideration is choosing what clothes to wear. Teenagers should purchase or choose the clothes they want to wear. It could be because of fashion, formal meetings, or school. Otherwise, they may lose their individuality by only listening to other people's advice.

Admittedly, people might contend that a teenager is not mature enough to make decisions. But they overlook that teenagers nowadays are already mature enough to make life-changing decisions.

In conclusion, although there are concerns about teenagers' immaturity, I maintain that teenagers should make their own decisions, whether in education or clothing choices.
